ernal logic of such ideology, its genealogy, and its main contemporary incarnations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Neuroscience.2bisacsh  aNeurocultures.  abrain sciences.  acerebral subject.  amental disorder.  aneurocentrism.  aneurodiversity.  aneuroimaging.  aneuroscience and culture.  apersonal identity.  asubjectivation.1 aOrtega, Francisco, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311072901640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823276097zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823276097423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823276097/original  a978-3-11-072901-6  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK